cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS. 

The paper is about optimizing deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents experiments on image classification (CIFAR) and natural language inference (SNLI), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The optimization method proposed in the paper is based on a composite proximal framework, which is a mathematical optimization technique, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
